	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=classes.html?class=3&mid=99304984486574>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=3&mid=99304984486574>RE: AC or Agi ?</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=3&mid=99304984486574#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Wed, Jun 20th 11:10 AM 2001</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=39551><span id=Guru>Osano</span></a><br><b><span id=Guru>Guru</span></b><br><span id=notbold>171 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [4.11]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Agi will translate into more AC, although I don't know the exact formula.&nbsp;&nbsp;Basially, though, raw AC is better than AGI.<br><br>That being said, if you're overweight, it's a good idea to start working your way back towards your limit, even at the expense of raw AC.  This is, of course, because your AC will suffer from being overweight, typically more than it's worth.<br><br>If you're currently wearing raw-hide, leather, or whatever (very typical for low-level), the best thing to do is start swapping out pieces for cured silk or Wu's as you can afford them.  Being somewhat overweight won't seriously impact you at a low level, so there's no rush -- just something to start working on.</p>&nbsp;<br>Osano<br>Level 44 Human Monk<br>Tholuxe-Paells</td></td></tr>
