<table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0><tr><td>
	     <table class=mform  border=0 cellpadding=1 cellspacing=0 width=100%>
	     <form action=/cgi-bin/mrate.pl name=f99287449438158>
	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=classes.html?class=3&mid=99287449438158>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=3&mid=99287449438158>RE: Chat terms</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=3&mid=99287449438158#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Mon, Jun 18th 10:28 AM 2001</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=39551><span id=Guru>Osano</span></a><br><b><span id=Guru>Guru</span></b><br><span id=notbold>171 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [2.65]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Proc = special ability of a weapon to cast some type of spell, that is not under the direct control of the user.&nbsp;&nbsp;Monk weapons that 'proc' include Adamantite Bo (2HB with AOE effect) and Wu's Trance Stick (1HB with DD effect).  You have no control over when the weapon's effect will 'proc' (go off), but a high DEX will make it proc slightly more often.  Sometimes a weapon will proc zero times in a fight, sometimes a lot.  <br><br>Some items have an 'Effect' that *is* under the direct control of the user, by right clicking on the item.  One monk favorite of this type is the Crystallized Pumice, which has the effect of Cancel Magic.  This is awesome for bringing down the damage shield of a nasty opponent.  Pumice can be bought from magic-item vendors in most major cities for about 16PP for 5 charges.  Yes, expensive, but when you are at a high level, and fighting certain key opponents without someome who can cancel magic, well worth the cash.<br><br>Twinked = a character who has been given the benefit of vastly superior weaponry and/or armor for his level.  This is typically done by someone with a high level character who has lots of extra cash to spend or great items to use.  They give this to a new character to give him a head start.  This is called Twinking.  Untwinked simply means that everything your character has, has been earned by that character.  Needless to say, everyone's FIRST character is 'Untwinked', unless they have a friend on the server who is willing to dump a bunch of equimpent on them, which does happen fairly often.</p>&nbsp;<br>Osano<br>Level 44 Human Monk<br>Tholuxe-Paells</td></td></tr>
