	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=35651><span id=Guru>Keyeluke</span></a><br><b><span id=Guru>Guru</span></b><br><span id=notbold>679 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [4.60]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>I hunted Ogre Island briefly, though I'm pretty sure I was higher than 15 when I did.&nbsp;&nbsp;It's pretty good hunting, but be warned:  there are some higher level mobs there, and you have no place to run if things get messy.  You don't have your Feign Death yet, either.  And, if memory serves, you may end up sitting on your butt a lot waiting for mobs to respawn.<br><br>Try it once - see how you like it.  Personally, I'd say you're better off in Oasis for now - at least there you can bolt for a zone if there's trouble, and there are a lot more critters to choose from.  The crocs range widely in levels, so you can pick and choose what you fight based on the strength of your group, and the orc highway is always busy.<br><br>Keyeluke <br>Monk of the Silent Fist, 45th Circle <br>Strange Brew <br>Druzzil Ro <br></p>&nbsp;<br>Keyeluke<br>Member of Tenacity - Druzzil Ro<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=27415" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=27415</a></td></td></tr>
