	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Sat, Jun 16th 10:58 PM 2001</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=39551><span id=Guru>Osano</span></a><br><b><span id=Guru>Guru</span></b><br><span id=notbold>171 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [2.20]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>True, plus, even if you're getting exp, if the mob is a green con, your chance for a skill increase is VERY small.&nbsp;&nbsp;Basically you need to be fighting at least blue cons for a decent skill-up rate.  This applies to your main fighting skills -- certain skills like Disarm and Instill Doubt CAN be practiced against no-exp greens.<br><br>A simple low-risk way to get your 2HB up is to find a full group fighting something that cons blue to low red to you, and ask if you can fight outside the group with your 2HB for practice.  Note that you could hardly KS a full group this way so most people will be happy to get a bit of free damage from you.  You won't get any exp while practicing, but your 2HB will go up quickly, to the point where you can actually use it in an exp group or solo.</p>&nbsp;<br>Osano<br>Level 44 Human Monk<br>Tholuxe-Paells</td></td></tr>
